      <div class="story-container">
        <h2 class="section-title">The Story Behind Read Labels</h2>
        <div class="story-text">
          <p>The idea for Read labels came from a common frustration I observed: people standing in store aisles, squinting at product labels, trying to decipher complex ingredient lists. Many would eventually give up and make purchases based on marketing claims rather than actual ingredients.</p>
          <p>As someone with a background in both development and design, I realized I could create a solution that bridges this gap. Read labels is the result - a simple tool that scans product labels and breaks down the information in plain language, helping you decide if a product is worth buying based on your personal needs and expectations.</p>
          <p>This is my first project as a backend developer, combining my passion for creating intuitive user experiences with practical problem-solving. By leveraging technology to decode ingredient lists, Read labels empowers consumers to make informed choices without needing a chemistry degree.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="mission-container">
        <h3 class="mission-title">My Mission</h3>
        <div class="mission-text">
          <p>I believe that everyone deserves to know what they're putting in and on their bodies in terms they can actually understand. My mission with Read labels is to demystify product labels and empower consumers to make choices aligned with their personal values and health priorities.</p>
          <p>By translating complicated ingredient lists into clear, actionable information, Read Lables helps bridge the gap between manufacturers and consumers. Whether you have specific allergies, are looking for more natural products, or simply want to know what you're buying, Read labels puts that information at your fingertips.</p>
        </div>
